Description:
Stylish Inner City living…
Located at the ‘Paris’ end of Collingwood this beautifully presented 2 bedroom contemporary town residence offers a lifestyle to savour just a stroll to the delights of Smith & Brunswick Streets with their diverse eateries, eclectic specialty shops and myriad of public transport options. Part of a 3 lot subdivision each with their own street frontage and possessing a unique architecturally designed façade with a distinct industrial edge, this delightful abode is bathed in Northerly light and is certainly an entertainer’s delight enjoying huge open plan living areas adjoining a substantial outdoor balcony. Other features include rich timber floors, reverse cycle heating/cooling, alarm system fully equipped kitchen and lock up garage.
Insights: 61 Mater Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2011 and 29 other 2 bedroom house in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Chic Inner-City Indulgence
A luxurious lifestyle sanctuary graced by grandeur and awash with romance; this sumptuous warehouse conversion resembles a boutique Parisian hotel with soaring 6m ceilings, crystal chandeliers and high-wall ch teau courtyard with auto off street parking. A divine transformation of unparalleled quality and style elevates this opulent home into another realm where everyday living and entertaining are a pleasure and a privilege. Finishes of marble, raw travertine and onyx combine with superior features highlighting remarkable attention to detail. Boasts three bedrooms (third or home office), three bathrooms (two ensuites), living room, family lounge and dining areas, stunning kitchen and roof terrace. City-fringe convenience near cafes, shops, transport and parkland.
Inspect by appointment.
Belinda Lindsay : 0409 853 769

Description:
The Perfect Start
An ideal way for first home buyers to reach square one in style or a superb opportunity for astute investors to reap reliable inner-city rewards. Either way, this charming brick two-bedroom terrace offers an exceptional future. Its appealing spaces, perfectly comfortable at present, provide scope for further improvement and include sunny central living area leading to bright separate kitchen with access to a brick paved rear courtyard. Two double bedrooms, both with period open fireplaces, one with access to ample in-roof storage and main with built-in-robe, are served by a functional bathroom and complete the perfect ownership debut or investment portfolio addition close to great shopping on Smith Street, schools, parks and transport to the city. This is entry-level buying at its very best.
Leonard Siragusa : 0407 875 048

Description:
Chic City Cutie
For Sale By Private Bid Closing Tuesday 1st March at 5pm
This gorgeous residence is a must see prospect for any type of buyer! Astute investors and progressive downsizers will delight at the home’s versatility, while first home buyers will surely appreciate its amazing price. Found on the ground floor, the well-presented abode features sun-filled living areas and a clever floorplan comprising a spacious lounge room, vividly-hued kitchen, integrated bathroom/laundry, separate WC, and sleeping wing with 2 generous bedrooms. Apart from the convenience of being able to walk to Smith and Brunswick streets from this superbly positioned dwelling, the key characteristic of living here is access to the large roof-top terrace – a place where enjoying a glass of red as the sun sets over the city views is inevitable. Be quick to take advantage of this hot property before someone else does!
Features: heater in lounge room, single lock-up garage, 2 generous bedrooms (1 with BIRs), access to large roof-top terrace with city views, within walking distance to Victoria Park Station, Smith Street, Brunswick Street, Victoria Park and Darling Gardens.
Presented by PhilipWebb Real Estate.

Description:
Room to Groove!
With Summer fast approaching and inner city rooftop courtyards rare, you will love the spaces this huge split-level apartment provides.
Set over two generous levels comprising a sleek modern kitchen with double pantry, ample bench space, built in microwave, stainless steel appliances including dishwasher & gas cook top. A spacious open plan living dining room with soaring cathedral ceilings will house all of your entertainment and loads of natural light beckons you onto the large private terrace that's perfect for entertaining, BBQ's or winding down. A/C, a study nook, laundry and handy powder room also complete the upper level.
Downstairs you'll find the two bedrooms, both with robes, natural light and the master with en-suite.
Heating & cooling, secured entrance, lift access, 2 secure car parks, a storage cage, convenient inner city location, close to transport, shops , the CBD and all its treats, get ready to enjoy the best the inner city has to offer.

Description:
When size matters.
This spacious apartment in the Islington building, Collingwood street gives you modern styling, and the best of locations, and it is fully furnished in style too.
With two generous bedrooms inviting bright easterly light, the property is fresh and clean, and will appeal to investors and occupiers alike. The spacious living and dining gives you a retreat from the hustle and bustle, and opens out onto a neat terrace for entertaining and fresh air. The kitchen is fully appointed with fridge, 4 gas burner, fan forced oven and extractor fan, with heaps of storage for your culinary dreams. Both bedrooms offer comfort with built in robes, the master with A/C, and are cleverly seperated to maximise the privacy of residents. With two generous bathrooms on offer, one a sparkling ensuite off the master ,and another large central bathroom with fully appointed laundry, there's no worrying over who uses the bathroom first, problem solved!
Perfectly located near public transport and the major arterials, this property gives you the choice of leaving the car at home, or hitting the road without any fuss. And when you are only ten minutes from the CBD by bike or tram, the carspace is going to come in handy.

Description:
RARE, UN-RENOVATED INNER CITY VICTORIAN
A classical cottage in the very heart of Collingwood, this captivating Victorian is an entry level opportunity that makes perfect sense from either lifestyle or investment perspectives.
An intimate original floor-plan features a bright double bedroom and a separate study arranged around a central living/dining space beneath traditional high ceilings.
A serviceable older style kitchen and spacious, similarly functional bathroom complete current day spaces while a courtyard conclusion completes a tempting opportunity!
Openings such as this, where potential and position form such a compelling combination, are increasingly un-common - and will only become more so with the passage of time.
Proximity to the CBD, Smith Street shops and trams and the cafe culture that defines Brunswick Street makes this evocative cottage an even more tempting proposition!
Jason Sharpe : 0438 847 700

Description:
Exciting Possibilities in Enviable Location
Brilliantly situated on a north oriented corner site offering close proximity to Smith and Johnson Streets' vibrant shops and cafes and the CBD, this single level solid-brick contemporary residence represents an exciting renovation or redevelopment opportunity
with the possibility of constructing up to 3 town-residences (STCA).
Currently in completely comfortable condition, it features wide entrance hall through to living/study, light-filled living and dining room boasting vaulted ceilings and a capable kitchen opening out to private north-facing garden. Six spacious bedrooms (BIRs) are complemented by two bright bathrooms and laundry. Also features RC/air-conditioning and OSP.
An outstanding inner urban opportunity.
